<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I would say to make use of your summoned pet and try soloing in Paludal Caverns.  As you enter the zone, haste your pet and cast your regent free rune (Berserker Strength or something) on it and yourself.  You can tackle the mushroom near the entrance to the C1 camp.  Tash it, and it will come after you.  Pet, of course, will attack once you're attacked.  After your pet has beat on it a few times, back up and cast your slow on it.  You'll probably have to re Berserker your pet, so do that next and then DoT. You can nuke, once your certain your pet can hold onto aggro.  Or you can take up a weapon and start building your skills on it.   <br /> <br />Once the mushroom is dead, you can take on Yelloweyes in the same manner.  You'll find him right after the cave entrance to the C1 area of the zone, unless the groups in PC have already gotten to him. <br /> <br />I wouldn't actually go into the camps themselves, since you're determined to solo it.  But invis your way through it (pet doesn't need it) and head toward the caves.  You'll find a mushroom and plenty of fiends to play with.  With the use of your pacify spell and mezz, you'll have plenty of fiends to occupy your time and shouldn't need to tackle any more than one at a time.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
