<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Learn to charm early.  Charm rules!!!! <br /> <br />I'll write a small guide for charming in the Paludal Caverns. <br /> <br />You will need to be at least level 13 with your first charm spell &quot;Charm&quot;.  This will allow you charm any mob up to level 25.  No mobs in Paludals are higher than 24.  This works out perfectly. <br /> <br />You will also need your first Rune spell.  Rune I.  Casting this spell will cost you a Cat's Eye Agate.  Pick up a few stacks, they're really cheap, and will save your life.   <br /> <br />Before you head off, get the following.  Clarity, Temperance, a Cha buff, and if you can find a nice enchanter, a Rune IV. <br /> <br />Here is my spell line up:  <br />Tashanian <br />Forlorn Deeds <br />Greater Fetter <br />Apathy <br />Beckon <br />Arcane Rune <br />Rune of Zebuxoruk <br />Dementia <br />Improved Invisibility <br /> <br />It's understandable that you wont have your 9th spell gem.  The reason I have mine setup that way is I use the hotbutton bank to cast my spells <br />1.  Root <br />2.  Nuke <br />3.  Mez <br />4.  Charm <br /> <br />Set yours up however you like. <br />------------- <br />Head down to the Paludal Caverns.  Go past Camp 1 where everyone and their mother is and go up the walk way.  If you see the roamer, he will make a suitable pet.  If not, keep going up the ramp and grab the one that hides by the sharp upward facing rock things, right before the corner. <br /> <br />Whenever you charm anything, cast you highest Tashan spell on it first.  This will ensure that your Charm lasts for the maximum amount of time.  I wont explain why, but trust me, it does.  Cast your best haste on him after you have him charmed. <br /> <br />Now that you have your pet, walk him up to the ramp.  Tell him to sit, and go find your target.  DO NOT INVIS.  Invis'ing will break your charm, and you will have one pissed off fiend coming after you. <br /> <br />Find your target and cast your best slow on him.  This will have him running after you.  Run back to your pet and root your target.  Then tell your pet to attack.  Back up and watch your pet chew through this mob.  If your pet gets hit and loses some HP's, thats good. Thats what you want.  The whole point to this is to have your pet kill other mobs, while other mobs, kill your pet at the same time.  That way you can break charm and nuke him a few times, he'll die, and you get full exp. <br /> <br />Ideally, your pet could go through about 7 mobs before he's low enough to get killed if you're Hasting your pet, and slowing your targets. <br /> <br />Once your pet is low enough to start running away, invis yourself to break charm and root him.  Make sure you stand away from him when you do this because he is still hasted.  Start nuking and he'll run away again.  Keep nuking him dead, and you'll get full experience as if you killed him yourself. <br /> <br />Make sure you always have some form of Rune on you for when he breaks.  It will save your life.  You could solo all the way to 65 (or 70 if you have patience) with this.  The only thing that changes is the zone, level of mobs, and the amount of exp.  Get good at it fast, and learn to love it. <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Fri May 27 11:57:41 2005 by ghengisjon</span></i></p>
