<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>I think a good soloing guide is a true soloing guide. <br /> <br />What do I mean by that? It means forget the buffs. You need to learn to solo on your own without buffs from another player. What happens when that mob you just dotted dispells your temp/virt?  <br /> <br />Solo means you have to adjust yourself to survive on your own. If you do fine with buffs and kick the bucket without them, you're not soloing. <br /> <br />A real solo is a true solo. If you can't play on just your own buffs it's not soloing. This guide should take that into consideration.</p>
