<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Meh, I really think if you're going to solo, just go do it. Now, if I'm pet soloing with Shiny Bob, I'll likely go and grab some mage-summoned pet gear (since that can't be dispelled), but if I'm going to go charm kiting, I just buff up and go... the only catch being that I use a SoW bottle and place it last on my buff list, but I always have one on me anyways for general utility. <br /> <br />Now, I tend to die with some regularity if I'm going to charm solo, so I don't see the need to beg or buy buffs OR buff potions, because I never know when the next death will hit, and it makes no sense to get all buffed up just do die and lose all the plat you just spent on buffs. Yes, I know, maybe those buffs will prevent a death, but it still happens pretty regularly even when buffed... being buffed up might prevent perhaps one out of four deaths for me, but who's to say which one? <br /> <br />I guess my point is, if you're going to go solo, just pick up and go. Grab the bare minimum you'll NEED (i.e. pet gear if you're gonna use your summoned pet), buff yourself, and get soloing instead of wasting time begging for Conviction in the PoK. <br /> <br />Really, though, if you're smart, you'll give soloing the finger, grab a ranger or druid, and REALLY put away the mobs charming with their snares... I'm yet to die doing this, there's fewer people to share loot with, and I make better XP sometimes than I get in whole groups! ;)</p>
