<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I guess I am still a baby chanter as I am only 47, but I will give you my 2 coppers worth. <br /> <br />Myself in the 18 - 24 range I was running around in Unrest.  I have spent time in Lake of Ill Omen, Echo Caverns and Overthere. <br /> <br />One I got to about 32 to 35 I moved to the beaches in Gunthak and have been there until about 44.   <br /> <br />At 44 I started working the entry canyon and the wall area of Dulak.   <br /> <br />My sisters thought I would get creamed in both Gunthak and Dulak but I was able to solo both areas.  When I can I try to pick up a Temperance, but I found that when they dropped I could self-buff my pet and myself and still work both of those areas.  Granted I have to spend a little more time medding or healing, but it is possible. <br /> <br />My pet I would just give him Rune, Cloud/Haze/Shadow, Haste, Strength, and a Damage Shield.  For myself I would add the appropriate Shielding and away we would go.   <br /> <br />I would pull with a Slow then let my pet engage and Weaken the mob.  Once my pet had softened him up a little I would hit him a form of the Anarchy or two until he came onto me and then duked it out with my pet getting max shots from behind. <br /> <br />Sounds crazy but it worked for me and my 1hb is maxed at 110, Dodge at 75 (too low of a max if you ask me), while my Off at 126 and my Def at 141. <br /> <br />I know that most people reading this already know these things but I hope that it helps some of the newbies out there.</p>
